    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In Buddhism, the final nirvana or nirvana-after-death, which occurs upon the death of the body or ultimate departure from the conventional realm of a person who is an awakened being, having attained nirvana during his or her lifetime.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
